<sect2 id="file-fli-export">
  <title>Export Image as FLI Animation</title>

  <indexterm>
    <primary>Export Image as FLI Animation</primary>
  </indexterm>
  <indexterm>
    <primary>Formats</primary>
    <secondary>fli</secondary>
  </indexterm>

  <sect3>
    <title>Overview</title>

    <figure>
      <title>The FLI Animation Export dialog</title>
      <mediaobject>
        <imageobject>
          <imagedata format="PNG"
            fileref="images/dialogs/export-fli-dialog.png"/>
        </imageobject>
      </mediaobject>
    </figure>

    <para>
      The FLI format was used by Autodesk Animator to store animation files.
      It was a widely used animation format in the 1990s.
    </para>
  </sect3>

  <sect3>
    <title>Options</title>

    <variablelist>
      <varlistentry>
        <term>From frame</term>
        <listitem>
          <para>
            The first frame (layer) to include.
          </para>
        </listitem>
      </varlistentry>
      <varlistentry>
        <term>To frame</term>
        <listitem>
          <para>
            The last frame (layer) to include, or -1 for all frames.
          </para>
        </listitem>
      </varlistentry>
    </variablelist>
  </sect3>

</sect2>
